    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-02-14T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-02-14T02:00:00-05:00" n="679"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d679">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.00111 <hi rend="superscript">Armament
                        Control/Military Secrets</hi>/1535: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_KAC1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-02-14T10:00:00+03:00"
                            >February 14, 1939—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 14—6:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>72. Embassy today granted diplomatic visa to Issaakov, Assistant Commissaire for
                    Navy Fleet of the U. S. S. R., and non-immigrant section 3 (1) visas to the
                    seven members of that Commissariat who are accompanying him to the United States
                    for what was described in the Foreign Office note as a “special mission for the
                    Soviet Navy”. The mission is expected to sail from Havre on February 25 on the
                        <hi rend="italic">Aquitania.</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Although no statement to that effect was forthcoming, it is assumed that this
                    mission relates to the matter discussed in my telegram No. 428, December 17, 9
                    a.m., 1938.<note n="71a" xml:id="d679fn71a">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_707">p. 707</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KAC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
